## [1.3.2-alpha] - 2026-03-01

### Code Quality: Type Safety & Naming Consistency (Sprint 21c)

#### Changed
- **Named struct tags for forward declarations**: `cast_server_t` (`struct cast_server_s`),
  `castv2_client_t` (`struct castv2_client_s`), `memory_t` (`struct memory_s`) now support
  proper C forward declarations instead of relying on `void*` hacks.
- **`audio_set_cast_server(void*)` → `audio_set_cast_server(cast_server_t*)`**: type-safe
  parameter replaces opaque `void*`, enabling compile-time type checking.
- **`cpu6502_t.memory` from `void*` to `memory_t*`**: strongly typed pointer replaces
  opaque `void*`, eliminating casts in `cpu6502.c` and `addressing.c`.
- **`cpu_init(cpu6502_t*, void*)` → `cpu_init(cpu6502_t*, memory_t*)`**: type-safe signature.
- **`pb_encode_enum` → `pb_encode_varint_field`** in `castv2.c`: name now accurately
  reflects that the function encodes any protobuf varint field, not just enums.
- **Unified `cast_server_` prefix**: `cast_upscale_nearest` → `cast_server_upscale_nearest`,
  `cast_build_mdns_query` → `cast_server_build_mdns_query`, `cast_build_wav_header` →
  `cast_server_build_wav_header`, `cast_discover_devices` → `cast_server_discover_devices`.
- **`handle_new_connection` → `route_http_request`** in `cast_server.c`: name reflects
  actual HTTP request routing responsibility.
- **`int` → `size_t`/`uint32_t` for sizes and positions**: `jpeg_len`/`jpeg_capacity` now
  `size_t`, `audio_write_pos`/`audio_read_pos` now `uint32_t`, `num_samples` now `size_t`,
  `buf_size` now `size_t`, `push_frame` width/height now `unsigned int`.
- **Removed broken forward declaration** `struct cast_server_t;` in `audio.h` (was declaring
  a different type than the actual typedef), replaced with correct `typedef struct cast_server_s`.
- **Removed unnecessary `(memory_t*)` casts** in `cpu6502.c` and `addressing.c`.
- 192 tests, 100% pass rate (no functional change)

## [1.3.1-alpha] - 2026-03-01

### WAV Audio Streaming for Chromecast (Sprint 21b)

#### Added
- **WAV audio streaming endpoint** (`GET /audio`): HTTP endpoint serving
  infinite WAV stream (mono PCM 16-bit, 44100 Hz) from PSG audio output.
  Enables Chromecast to play ORIC-1 sound via `<audio>` HTML element.
- **Audio ring buffer** in `cast_server_t`: 2-second circular buffer
  (`CAST_AUDIO_RING_SAMPLES = 88200`) with mutex-protected write access
  and per-client read positions (up to 4 audio clients).
- **Stereo-to-mono downmix**: `cast_server_push_audio()` receives stereo
  PCM from SDL2 audio callback and writes mono average to ring buffer.
- **WAV header builder** `cast_build_wav_header()`: generates 44-byte
  RIFF/WAV header with infinite data size (`0x7FFFFFFF`) for streaming.
- **Audio forwarding hook**: `audio_set_cast_server()` connects SDL2
  audio callback to cast server. Called from `audio_callback()` after
  `ay_generate()` to stream PSG audio in real-time.
- **HTML `<audio autoplay>`**: cast viewer page at `/` now includes
  `<audio autoplay><source src="/audio" type="audio/wav">` for automatic
  sound playback on Chromecast.
- **3 new audio streaming unit tests**: WAV header validity (44 bytes,
  RIFF/WAVE/fmt/data, PCM mono 44100 16-bit), ring buffer push (stereo
  downmix verification), ring buffer wrap-around (circular write).
- **Web Audio API low-latency playback**: HTML page uses `fetch()` with
  `ReadableStream` reader + `AudioContext` to decode PCM chunks and
  schedule playback with ~100ms buffer. Replaces `<audio>` element
  which had 2-5s browser buffering. Drift correction resets schedule
  if >500ms ahead. Autoplay with click fallback for Chrome policy.

#### Changed
- `cast_server.h`: added `CAST_AUDIO_*` constants, audio ring buffer
  fields, `audio_mutex`, `audio_clients[]`/`audio_read_pos[]` arrays,
  `cast_server_push_audio()` and `cast_build_wav_header()` declarations,
  stub for non-CAST builds.
- `cast_server.c`: `/audio` route with WAV header + streaming, audio
  client management, `broadcast_audio()` in server loop, audio mutex
  init/destroy in lifecycle.
- `audio_output.c`: `audio_set_cast_server()` implementation, cast
  server push call in SDL2 `audio_callback()`.
- `audio.h`: `audio_set_cast_server()` declaration.
- `main.c`: wiring `audio_set_cast_server()` after cast server init.
- Version updated from 1.3.0-alpha to 1.3.1-alpha.
- Total test count: 192 tests (189 + 3 audio streaming), 100% pass rate.

## [1.3.0-alpha] - 2026-02-28

### Native CASTV2 Client (Sprint 21)

#### Added
- **Native CASTV2 client** (`src/network/castv2.c`):
  Zero-dependency Google Cast V2 protocol implementation in C for direct
  Chromecast control without catt, Chromium, or any external tool.
- **Hand-coded protobuf** encoder/decoder for CastMessage (6 fields):
  `castv2_encode_varint()`, `castv2_decode_varint()`, `pb_encode_string()`,
  `pb_encode_enum()`, `castv2_build_message()` with 4-byte BE framing.
- **TLS connection** via OpenSSL: `SSL_VERIFY_NONE` for Chromecast self-signed
  certs, 5s socket timeout.
- **Cast protocol sequence** in `castv2_connect_and_cast()`:
  TLS connect → CONNECT receiver-0 → LAUNCH DashCast (appId 5C3F0A3C) →
  parse RECEIVER_STATUS for transportId → CONNECT transport → send URL.
- **Heartbeat thread**: PING every 5s to receiver-0 and transportId,
  clean shutdown via `heartbeat_running` flag + `pthread_join`.
- **mDNS discovery wrapper** `castv2_discover_device()`: find Chromecast
  by name filter, returns IP address.
- **Local IP detection** `castv2_get_local_ip()`: UDP connect to 8.8.8.8:53
  (no data sent) + `getsockname()` to determine LAN IP.
- **CLI option `--cast-to[=DEVICE]`**: cast to first Chromecast found or
  to specific device by name. Implicitly enables `--cast-server`.
- **8 new CASTV2 protobuf unit tests**: varint single/multi/roundtrip,
  build message, message framing, source ID, buffer too small, protocol version.
- **Simplified `cast-play.sh`**: uses native `--cast-to` instead of
  catt/Chromium. Reduced from ~340 to ~100 lines. Zero external dependencies.

#### Changed
- `cast_server.h`: added `castv2_state_t` enum, `castv2_client_t` struct,
  CASTV2 API functions and protobuf helpers, stubs for non-CAST builds.
- `emulator_t` struct: added `castv2_client_t castv2_client` and `has_castv2`.
- `emulator_cleanup()`: disconnects CASTV2 client (STOP → SSL shutdown).
- `Makefile`: CAST=1 now adds `-lssl -lcrypto`, compiles `castv2.c`.
- Version updated from 1.2.0-alpha to 1.3.0-alpha.
- Total test count: 189 tests (181 + 8 CASTV2), 100% pass rate.

#### Fixed
- **CASTV2 disconnect hang**: `castv2_disconnect()` no longer hangs on Ctrl+C.
  Uses `pthread_cancel()` for heartbeat thread (was blocked on `sleep(5)`),
  `shutdown(SHUT_RDWR)` before `SSL_free` (skips blocking `SSL_shutdown`).
- **CASTV2 session robustness**: STOP stale DashCast before LAUNCH, mutex
  protection on `SSL_write`, PING/PONG handling, `"origin":{}` in CONNECT.
- **Chromecast display**: HTML page uses `/snapshot` polling (50ms) instead of
  MJPEG `multipart/x-mixed-replace` which Chromecast browser doesn't support.
- **Keyboard layout**: `cast-play.sh` defaults to AZERTY (`-k azerty`).

## [1.2.0-alpha] - 2026-02-28

### MJPEG Cast Server + mDNS Chromecast Discovery (Sprint 20)

#### Added
- **MJPEG cast server** (`src/network/cast_server.c`, `include/network/cast_server.h`):
  HTTP MJPEG streaming server for casting the emulator display to a browser
  or Chromecast device via tab casting.
- **HTML viewer page** at `/`: fullscreen black background with pixelated
  `<img>` element pointing to `/stream`, styled for retro display.
- **MJPEG stream endpoint** at `/stream`: multipart/x-mixed-replace JPEG
  stream with 720x672 upscaled frames (3x nearest-neighbor from 240x224).
- **JPEG encoding**: uses vendored `stb_image_write.h` (public domain,
  Sean Barrett) for header-only JPEG encoding at quality 80.
- **Multi-client support**: up to 8 concurrent stream clients with
  `select()`-based non-blocking I/O and `MSG_NOSIGNAL` disconnect detection.
- **Thread-safe frame push**: `cast_server_push_frame()` upscales under
  mutex, JPEG encoding done in server thread outside mutex.
- **mDNS/DNS-SD discovery** (`cast_discover_devices()`): sends PTR query
  for `_googlecast._tcp.local` via UDP multicast to 224.0.0.251:5353,
  parses PTR/SRV/A/TXT records with DNS compression pointer support,
  displays device name (`fn=` from TXT), IP, and port.
- **CLI option `--cast-server[=PORT]`**: start MJPEG server (default 8080).
- **CLI option `--cast-discover`**: standalone mode, discover Chromecast
  devices on the network and exit.
- **Conditional build `CAST=1`**: adds `-DHAS_CAST -lpthread`, compiles
  `src/network/cast_server.c`. Without CAST=1, cast_server_t is a minimal
  stub and all functions are no-ops.
- **Vendored `third_party/stb_image_write.h`**: v1.16, public domain,
  no external dependency for JPEG encoding.
- **13 cast server unit tests** in `tests/unit/test_cast.c`:
  upscale (single pixel, 2x2 frame, color preservation), JPEG (non-zero
  length, SOI marker), server (lifecycle, port default), HTTP (HTML page
  content, MJPEG stream header), mDNS (query build, length, buffer too
  small), frame push ready flag.
- **`make test-cast`** target (requires CAST=1 implicitly via -DHAS_CAST).
- **Valgrind target** updated to include cast tests.

#### Changed
- `emulator_t` struct: added `cast_server_t cast_server` and `has_cast_server`
- `emulator_run()`: pushes frame to cast server after `video_render_frame()`
- `emulator_cleanup()`: stops cast server
- Version updated from 1.1.2-alpha to 1.2.0-alpha
- Total test count: 181 tests (168 + 13 cast), 100% pass rate

## [1.1.2-alpha] - 2026-02-27

### VSync CB1 Improvements (Sprint 19c)

#### Changed
- **PAL timing constants**: replaced `CYCLES_PER_FRAME = 1000000/50` (20000)
  with real PAL values: 312 lines x 64 cycles = 19968 cycles/frame.
  New constants: `PAL_LINES_PER_FRAME`, `PAL_CYCLES_PER_LINE`, `VSYNC_START_LINE`,
  `VSYNC_CYCLE` (16384 = line 256 x 64 cycles).
- **VSync mid-frame trigger**: VSync CB1 pulse now fires at line 256 (cycle
  16384) inside the frame loop instead of at the end of frame, matching real
  ULA timing. CB1 goes low (falling edge) at VSYNC_CYCLE, then returns high
  after the frame loop completes.
- **Edge-triggered CB1**: new `via_set_cb1()` function implements proper edge
  detection using PCR bit 4 (0=falling edge, 1=rising edge). IFR CB1 flag is
  only set on the correct edge transition. Added `cb1_pin` field to `via6522_t`.
- **Legacy `via_trigger_cb1()`**: refactored to use `via_set_cb1()` internally
  (complete pulse: high→low→high).
- **IER guard on VSync trigger**: emulation loop only generates VSync CB1 pulse
  when software has enabled CB1 in VIA IER (`emu->via.ier & VIA_INT_CB1`),
  preventing disruption of ROM keyboard scan IRQ timing.

#### Fixed
- **`via_check_irq()` transition-only notification**: the IRQ callback to the
  CPU is now called only when the /IRQ line state **changes** (assert→deassert
  or deassert→assert), not on every IFR/IER modification. Added `irq_line`
  field to `via6522_t` to track the current /IRQ output level. This prevents
  spurious `cpu_irq_clear(IRQF_VIA)` when unrelated IFR bits (e.g. CB1) change
  while no matching IER bit is set, which was causing loss of pending T1 IRQs
  and breaking the ROM keyboard scan.
- **Removed IER guards from VSync trigger**: CB1 now fires unconditionally
  like real hardware. Programs polling IFR bit 4 without enabling CB1 in IER
  will work correctly. The transition-only fix in `via_check_irq` makes this
  safe.

#### Added
- **5 new CB1 edge detection tests**: falling edge trigger, rising edge trigger,
  wrong edge no trigger, same state no trigger, clear and retrigger.
- Total: 168 tests (163 + 5), 100% pass rate.

## [1.1.1-alpha] - 2026-02-27

### VSync CB1 Signal (Sprint 19b)

#### Fixed
- **VSync signal on VIA CB1**: the ULA VSync pulse is now generated at the
  end of each frame (50 Hz) by calling `via_trigger_cb1()` in the emulation
  loop. On real Oric hardware, the ULA drives CB1 at vertical retrace so
  software can poll IFR bit 4 (`VIA_INT_CB1 = 0x10`) or enable the CB1
  interrupt to synchronize with the display. Previously this signal was never
  generated, causing programs relying on VBlank synchronization to malfunction.
- All 163 tests pass (no regression)

## [1.1.0-alpha] - 2026-02-24

### Interactive Debugger (Sprint 19)

#### Added
- **Interactive debugger module** (`src/debugger.c`, `include/debugger.h`):
  REPL-based debugger with stdin/stdout command interface
- **Breakpoints**: up to 16 PC breakpoints (`b addr`, `bd n`, `b` to list)
- **Watchpoints**: up to 8 memory write watchpoints (`w addr`, `wd n`, `w` to list)
  using `memory_set_trace()` callback for hardware-level detection
- **Single-step**: `s`/`step` executes one instruction and re-enters REPL
- **Step-over**: `n`/`next` steps over JSR (temporary breakpoint at PC+3)
- **Continue**: `c`/`continue` resumes execution until next breakpoint
- **Register display**: `r`/`regs` shows full CPU state (A,X,Y,SP,PC,P,cycles)
- **Disassembly**: `d [addr] [n]` disassembles n instructions from addr
- **Memory dump**: `m addr [len]` hex+ASCII dump
- **Stack display**: `stack` shows stack contents from SP to $01FF
- **VIA inspection**: `via` shows all VIA 6522 registers, timers, IRQ status
- **PSG inspection**: `psg` shows AY-3-8910 registers, channels, envelope
- **Register modification**: `set reg val` modifies CPU registers at runtime
- **Quit**: `q`/`quit` stops emulator from debugger
- **Help**: `h`/`help` shows command reference
- **`include/emulator.h`**: extracted `emulator_t` struct from `src/main.c`
  into shared header for access by debugger and future modules
- **CLI option `--debug` / `-D`**: start in debugger mode (break at first instruction)
- **CLI option `--break ADDR`**: set initial debugger breakpoint (hex address)
- **F9 key**: enter interactive debugger during SDL2 emulation
- **Legacy breakpoint promotion**: existing `-b`/`--breakpoint` now enters
  interactive debugger instead of halting
- **8 debugger unit tests** in `tests/unit/test_debugger.c`:
  init state, add/remove breakpoints, breakpoint limit (16 max),
  add/remove watchpoints, breakpoint hit/miss, step mode, disassembly
- **`make test-debugger`** target added
- **Valgrind target** updated to include debugger tests

#### Changed
- `emulator_t` struct moved from `src/main.c` to `include/emulator.h`
- `emulator_t` now includes `debugger_t debugger` member
- Version updated from 1.0.0-rc to 1.1.0-alpha
- Makefile: added `src/debugger.c` to SOURCES, test-debugger target
- CMakeLists.txt: added DEBUGGER_SOURCES, debugger_tests target
- .gitignore: added `test_debugger`
- Test suite expanded from 155 to 163 tests (155 + 8 debugger)
- Total test count: 163 tests, 100% pass rate

